1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,340
(Episode 91)

2
00:00:21,890 --> 00:00:23,060
It looks perfect on you.

3
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:25,930
Should we take a picture?

4
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:29,700
One...

5
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,940
Come on,
are you going to keep making that face?

6
00:00:33,410 --> 00:00:36,010
We need to get Baek Ho off our backs,
so play along.

7
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:41,610
Look here.

8
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,080
One, two, three!

9
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:46,220
Look right at the camera.

10
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:48,090
One, two!

11
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:51,320
We're getting married.

12
00:00:51,460 --> 00:00:53,660
We'll be handing out
the invitations in person soon.

13
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:00,200
Oh my, Baek Ho, look at this.

14
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:02,570
Don't they look perfect together?

15
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:05,500
They look like they belong together.

16
00:01:14,610 --> 00:01:16,450
Don't you like the wedding dress?

17
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:19,950
What does it matter
whether I like it or not?

18
00:01:20,550 --> 00:01:22,720
This wedding dress
is the least of my worries.

19
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:27,090
- Jang Mi.
- Let's just stay out of each other's way,

20
00:01:27,430 --> 00:01:28,890
regardless of how we feel
about each other.

21
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:33,630
You said Lawyer Han was coming
for the hanbok fitting, right?

22
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:37,300
Yes. She should be at the CEO's office.

23
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,010
I don't care what anyone says.

24
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:50,010
No matter how loudly my reason screams no,

25
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:51,720
I...

26
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,320
I can't fight it.

27
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,050
My heart...

28
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:58,720
only runs to you, Hwa Young.

29
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:01,490
I've lost the battle with myself.

30
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:05,830
So please, Hwa Young, you have to help me.

31
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:09,700
Professor Kang...

32
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:13,200
Should we just run away
somewhere together?

33
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:15,070
I want to.

34
00:02:15,770 --> 00:02:19,510
I want to disappear to somewhere
in the world with you, Nam Bong.

35
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,280
Hwa Young.

36
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:23,880
I love you.

37
00:02:24,950 --> 00:02:25,980
I love you.

38
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:33,890
I love you, too.

39
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:37,600
I love you, Nam Bong.

40
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:42,600
You're the first person
to ever make me feel like a real woman.

41
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:44,870
I love you more than anyone in the world.

42
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,250
What do you two think you're doing?

43
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:58,920
Mrs. Han...

44
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,400
Mrs. Han...

45
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,240
- Get your filthy hands off her!
- Honey!

46
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,890
Honey?

47
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:36,820
Did you just call me honey?
You crazy bastard! You filthy animal!

48
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:38,320
What are you doing?

49
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:41,190
Shouldn't I be asking you that?

50
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:44,500
Acting like animals in the office!

51
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,900
You bastard!

52
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:52,500
How could you stab me in the back
like this?

53
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:54,710
I trusted you so much!

54
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:58,980
There's a limit to how much of a fool
you can make me.

55
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,850
How could you do this?

56
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,550
Stop it!
You're a lawyer, for crying out loud!

57
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:07,520
Why act like an uneducated woman
off the street?

58
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:11,420
Mrs. Han.
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

59
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,060
We were just...

60
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,390
Mrs. Han?

61
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:19,400
Don't you "Mrs. Han" me, you tramp!

62
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:21,730
While you're supposedly trying
to marry off your daughter,

63
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,840
you couldn't find another man to seduce?

64
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:25,540
You had to go after my husband?

65
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,610
The nerve of you, deceiving me like this!

66
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,380
You have some nerve.

67
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,410
How could you swallow the food we ate?

68
00:04:33,410 --> 00:04:35,510
Could you? You tramp!

69
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:37,880
You filthy tramp!

70
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,920
Hey! Stop acting so uncivilized!

71
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,150
Get off me!

72
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,290
Uncivilized?

73
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,930
Am I not a person
just because I'm a lawyer?

74
00:04:48,530 --> 00:04:50,930
Am I supposed to stay calm and classy...

75
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,430
even after catching you two like this?

76
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
And you,

77
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,040
the so-called professor,

78
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,710
call having an affair being cultured?

79
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:02,810
Don't give me that crap about love!

80
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:05,740
What?

81
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:07,650
He made you "feel like a woman?"

82
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:11,350
You crazy tramp! You!

83
00:05:13,550 --> 00:05:15,750
Please stop. Let's go!

84
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:18,260
- Let's talk about this outside, okay?
- Let go of me!

85
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,990
Ripping out her hair wouldn't be enough.

86
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,230
Let go!

87
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:25,160
I won't let you two get away with this.
Let go of me!

88
00:05:25,230 --> 00:05:26,530
Let's just talk at home.

89
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:35,670
When Lawyer Han is done talking
with CEO Chae,

90
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:37,680
could you please ask her to text me?

91
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:40,310
I have something I'd like to ask her.

92
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:42,350
About what?

93
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,150
Just ask me.

94
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:49,390
Well, you and I are getting married now.

95
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,390
It's just that
I don't know the first thing...

96
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,390
about Lawyer Han's preferences.

97
00:05:58,230 --> 00:05:59,230
Honey,

98
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:02,530
I'm truly in love with Hwa Young.

99
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,070
What did you just say?

100
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,000
Professor Kang, stop.

101
00:06:07,210 --> 00:06:09,170
Young Ja, I'm so sorry.

102
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:11,210
I've been agonizing over this
for a long time.

103
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:13,110
Please, just try to understand.

104
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,450
You're telling the wife
who's stood by you...

105
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,450
that you're in love with another woman,

106
00:06:20,790 --> 00:06:22,550
and you expect me to understand that?

107
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,160
What if it were you?

108
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:28,090
If I said I loved another man,
would you be so quick to understand?

109
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:31,530
Mrs. Han, please calm down
and hear me out.

110
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:33,830
The children's marriage is my priority.

111
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:37,470
That's why,
because our children are in love,

112
00:06:38,670 --> 00:06:41,170
I was trying to end things
with Professor Kang for good.

113
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,140
You were ending things?
Then what was all that talk...

114
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:45,380
about him "making you feel like a woman"?

115
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,010
You really want to see
how far I can take this?

116
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:50,820
- Why, you...
- I said stop it!

117
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,420
Get out of my way!

118
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:55,650
If you're going to keep acting like this,

119
00:06:56,490 --> 00:06:58,460
then let's just end it.

120
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:01,960
What?

121
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:03,360
I'm...

122
00:07:04,030 --> 00:07:05,730
truly in love with Hwa Young,

123
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,400
- so divorce me, Young Ja.
- What are you doing, Professor Kang?

124
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,600
What?

125
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,400
Did you just...

126
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:15,010
ask me for a divorce?

127
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:16,970
Have you completely...

128
00:07:17,810 --> 00:07:19,580
lost your mind,

129
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:23,110
when you should be on your hands and knees
begging for my forgiveness?

130
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:24,450
For...

131
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,620
the last 30-some years,

132
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,920
we've had a good life together
raising our kids.

133
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:34,130
But now I've found my true love.

134
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,330
I just hope you can understand how I feel,
even now.

135
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,930
Professor Kang,
what do you think you're saying to her?

136
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:43,870
How could you say something like that?

137
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:47,940
- Unbelievable...
- You can...

138
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:49,510
take the house, the car,

139
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,880
and all the assets we built together.
You can have it all.

140
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:54,580
I...

141
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,680
can't live without Hwa Young.
I can't breathe.

142
00:07:58,020 --> 00:08:00,650
Do you have any idea how hard I've tried
to stay away from her?

143
00:08:01,590 --> 00:08:02,990
I just can't take it anymore.

144
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:06,720
- Hwa Young is all I need.
- Stop it!

145
00:08:07,690 --> 00:08:09,960
Mrs. Han, I swear, it's not like that.

146
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,660
Professor Kang and I
are not involved in any way.

147
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:16,170
- You're completely misunderstanding.
- A misunderstanding?

148
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:18,870
So, let me get this straight.

149
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:21,840
According to you, Chae Hwa Young,

150
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:25,440
you never had an affair
with Kang Nam Bong.

151
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:27,710
Does that mean
Kang Nam Bong is some stalker...

152
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:31,020
who's acting like a lunatic on his own?
Is that it?

153
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:33,990
Yes.

154
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,260
Hwa Young...

155
00:08:37,690 --> 00:08:39,890
That's not true.
We're in love with each other.

156
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:42,530
But here's the thing.

157
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:45,460
I already caught you in the act,

158
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,830
and I heard all those
filthy, pathetic words.

159
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,340
I heard every single word.

160
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:53,770
And as you can see,

161
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:56,140
Kang Nam Bong is admitting to it all.

162
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:59,910
Fine. I'll admit that much.

163
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:03,610
- I told you to stop!
- Hwa Young.

164
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,350
I know you're in a tough spot right now.

165
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:09,450
But just think of all the time
and the memories we've shared.

166
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,520
Shut up!

167
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:14,560
Your pathetic love story...

168
00:09:15,690 --> 00:09:16,790
I don't want to hear it!

169
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,500
It's always the same story.

170
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,740
The same one I've seen over and over...

171
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:29,110
in all the divorce cases I've handled.

172
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:30,780
It's unbelievable...

173
00:09:31,210 --> 00:09:33,540
to see it play out again
with the exact same script!

174
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,850
I can see why you would misunderstand.

175
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:40,180
Professor Kang is a good man, you know.
He's so kind and warm.

176
00:09:40,990 --> 00:09:41,990
I...

177
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:45,560
After my husband passed away,
I was so lonely,

178
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,260
and then I got to know Professor Kang.

179
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:50,700
For a little while at first,

180
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,030
I'll admit that
I did have feelings for him.

181
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:57,470
That's right, Hwa Young.
It was love at first sight.

182
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:02,110
But that's as far as it ever went
between Professor Kang and I.

183
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:04,610
When our children started talking
about marriage,

184
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:08,210
I put a stop to it for their sake.

185
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,420
That was your decision, Hwa Young.
Not mine.

186
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:14,290
I never even approved
of our kids getting married.

187
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:18,520
We were still involved after that,
weren't we?

188
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:22,060
- I said who cares if we become in-laws?
- That's enough!

189
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,500
I've heard enough...

190
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,930
of this sob story of yours.

191
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:30,370
Kang Nam Bong.

192
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:34,770
So that's why you were against
our kids getting married.

193
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,080
Now it all makes sense.

194
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:40,780
All right, fine.

195
00:10:42,410 --> 00:10:43,950
The wedding is off.

196
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:46,020
If they go through with it on their own,

197
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:49,390
I suppose I can't stop them.

198
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:54,590
But with my Jun Ho's sharp
and decisive personality,

199
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:56,530
do you really think
he'll go through with it?

200
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,370
Kang Nam Bong, as for the divorce papers,

201
00:11:04,170 --> 00:11:05,500
I'll draw them up myself.

202
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,040
Mom.

203
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:16,050
Mrs. Han, I can explain everything.

204
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,480
Just hear me out.

205
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:20,150
There's nothing
between Professor Kang and me.

206
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:24,520
Nothing between you?

207
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,590
Then why were you two hugging
and whispering words of love?

208
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,590
How disgusting.

209
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:36,000
You were all over my husband,

210
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:37,570
making a scene, and what?

211
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:39,470
You talk about our kids' wedding?

212
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,670
Listen here, Chae Hwa Young.

213
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,310
This wedding...

214
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,380
is absolutely not happening.

215
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,010
And you just wait.

216
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:49,610
I'm going to make you
take full responsibility...

217
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,580
for destroying my family.

218
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:53,220
You'd better be prepared.

219
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:57,760
- No, that's not it, Lawyer Han.
- That's enough, CEO Chae.

220
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:00,620
Mom, let's go.

221
00:12:24,450 --> 00:12:26,380
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

222
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,520
I'm sorry, Jang Mi.

223
00:12:28,690 --> 00:12:30,960
I had no idea
my father and CEO Chae were like that.

224
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:33,660
So what are we going to do now?

225
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:37,190
Our parents are having an affair
and chaos has erupted.

226
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,530
First, I need to go see CEO Chae.

227
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,810
- Hwa Young.
- I told you we should stop!

228
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:53,010
Did we need to break our kids' hearts?

229
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:54,610
Frankly, I think this is for the best.

230
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:59,080
People get divorced all the time.
So what if a wedding gets called off?

231
00:12:59,950 --> 00:13:02,750
I took in someone else's abandoned child
and raised him.

232
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,590
I've done my part.

233
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:07,320
I'm the one who abandoned Jun Ho.

234
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:11,830
I have to fulfill my duty
as his mother, too.

235
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,000
I'm going to get a divorce.

236
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:16,400
Now that it's out, I want to be with you.

237
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,470
Are you out of your mind?

238
00:13:17,470 --> 00:13:21,540
I can't live without you, Hwa Young.

239
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,280
You should leave
while I'm still being nice.

240
00:13:36,150 --> 00:13:37,150
Hwa Young.

241
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:39,020
I'll leave for today.

242
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,720
But...

243
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:42,860
my feelings for you...

244
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:44,760
have only grown stronger.

245
00:13:45,530 --> 00:13:46,530
Alright?

246
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,080
Hey.

247
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,980
If you keep saying you love CEO Chae,

248
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,890
I'll make you pay.

249
00:14:09,290 --> 00:14:10,290
Got it?

250
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:14,560
Father.

251
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:23,400
Father, is it really true?

252
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,640
You and the CEO Chae?

253
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,670
Why would you do that?

254
00:14:31,340 --> 00:14:32,440
I'm so ashamed.

255
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:36,180
I think it's best
you call off the wedding.

256
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:38,720
Now that your mother knows,

257
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,790
the wedding will probably be impossible.

258
00:14:44,090 --> 00:14:45,090
Just accept it.

259
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,400
You...

260
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:59,070
What was going on
between you and my father?

261
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,840
Were you two really in love?

262
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,640
Jun Ho.

263
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,310
It's a misunderstanding.

264
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,280
It was all one-sided
on Professor Kang's part.

265
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:10,280
Is that your excuse for everything?
A "misunderstanding"?

266
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:13,580
There's a limit
to how much you can hurt my mother.

267
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,020
How could you do this? Just how?

268
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,660
What do you mean, "your mother?"

269
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:20,190
Jun Ho.

270
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:22,660
I'm your mother, too.

271
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:24,030
I gave birth to you.

272
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:27,460
Why won't you believe
your own birth mother?

273
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:30,170
And now, to top it all off,

274
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,170
an affair?

275
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,740
Please believe me, Jun Ho.
It's a misunderstanding.

276
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,310
What am I supposed to do...

277
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:40,680
when Professor Kang is the one
obsessed with me?

278
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,810
So, is it a crime to be beautiful?

279
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:46,880
But not every beautiful woman
goes around wrecking people's homes.

280
00:15:46,950 --> 00:15:48,790
Stay out of this.
You don't know what you're talking about.

281
00:15:49,690 --> 00:15:50,890
Jun Ho, I'm serious.

282
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,560
Professor Kang's feelings for me
were completely one-sided.

283
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,590
But of all the terrible timing,

284
00:15:55,930 --> 00:16:00,100
Lawyer Han Young Ja saw us.
It's the truth. Please believe me.

285
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:01,500
Do you really think...

286
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:05,040
I've ever trusted you for a single moment?

287
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:08,570
The woman who abandoned me
when I was just a baby?

288
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:10,470
How could I possibly trust you?

289
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,040
You...

290
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:16,210
just gave the woman
who spent her life raising me with love...

291
00:16:16,980 --> 00:16:18,920
a wound that will never heal.

292
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:20,920
Do you understand?

293
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:23,750
- Jun Ho.
- No...

294
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,290
You didn't just hurt my mother.

295
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,030
If my wedding gets called off
because of you,

296
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:31,960
you'll be giving me another scar...

297
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:36,000
that I'll have to carry
for the rest of my life.

298
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,370
So you need to make...

299
00:16:39,970 --> 00:16:41,570
this wedding happen,
no matter what it takes.

300
00:16:42,510 --> 00:16:45,910
That's the only thing
you can do for me right now.

301
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:49,010
Got it?

302
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,790
Mom, be careful.
You're going to hurt yourself.

303
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,840
You worthless bastard!

304
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:20,610
I can't believe
he'd stab me in the back like this.

305
00:17:27,990 --> 00:17:30,350
Mom, stop it.
You're going to hurt yourself.

306
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:34,960
You knew?

307
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,330
About the insane thing
your father was doing?

308
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:40,500
You knew, didn't you?

309
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:52,240
How could you do this?

310
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:58,020
You knew all along
and didn't give me a heads-up?

311
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,650
Mom...

312
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:03,050
Did you enjoy
making me look like an idiot?

313
00:18:06,490 --> 00:18:09,990
You must have thought I was so pathetic,

314
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:12,730
watching me act like an idiot
for your father.

315
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:17,300
This can't be happening!

316
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:20,800
This can't be happening!

317
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:25,940
I'm sorry, Mom.

318
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,380
I didn't want to upset you.

319
00:18:30,380 --> 00:18:31,450
I was hoping...

320
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:34,220
I could somehow change Dad's mind.

321
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,090
I'm sorry, Mom.

322
00:18:54,370 --> 00:18:56,770
Gosh, Mom.
You're working a part-time job now.

323
00:18:57,310 --> 00:19:01,110
- But isn't it hard?
- Suk Hee is having fun. It's not hard.

324
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:03,410
Suk Hee is good at her job.

325
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:05,950
The vegetables are so fresh.

326
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:11,050
She just cleans and packs ingredients,
so it's not hard.

327
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:13,520
You know hygiene is our top priority here,
right?

328
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:17,590
- All we do is serve customers with care.
- Right.

329
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:20,730
I think we've got many customers
because the place is so clean and modern.

330
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,830
- Young people are here, too.
- Well, it's a prime location.

331
00:19:25,570 --> 00:19:27,100
How's Jang Mi doing lately?

332
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,810
She must be having a hard time
after her breakup with Baek Ho.

333
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:31,210
Tell me about it.

334
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,410
She's going ahead with the wedding,

335
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,380
and there's nothing I can do for her
as her brother.

336
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,020
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

337
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,820
At this rate,

338
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,320
is my wedding to Jun Ho
going to be called off?

339
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:45,020
What am I going to do?

340
00:19:50,860 --> 00:19:53,660
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

341
00:20:00,370 --> 00:20:02,970
How was your mother when you left?

342
00:20:03,970 --> 00:20:05,140
She's taking it really hard, isn't she?

343
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:07,340
I waited until she took her medicine...

344
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,550
and fell asleep.

345
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,890
Just give up on marrying my brother.

346
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:17,120
Now that my mother knows,

347
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:19,090
there's no way this wedding can happen.

348
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,190
And CEO Chae will give up, too.

349
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:22,460
That's...

350
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:25,100
not my decision to make.

351
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:26,760
What did you say?

352
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:28,930
So even after all this,

353
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,270
you're not going to give up on
marrying my brother?

354
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:36,270
Why are you doing this?

355
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:40,080
I know perfectly well that
you want to live as Seo Rin...

356
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:41,910
is just an excuse.

357
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,620
Please, just stop, Jang Mi.

358
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:49,220
Jang Mi, just live for yourself.

359
00:20:50,090 --> 00:20:52,660
Do you really think you can be happy
in a marriage like this?

360
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:54,090
Happiness?

361
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:56,890
I haven't even thought about
something like that.

362
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,400
I have my own path,

363
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,000
and that is my only focus.

364
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,300
Jang Mi, please.

365
00:21:05,270 --> 00:21:06,940
It's not too late to stop.

366
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:11,640
It's reckless to walk down a path you know
will only make you miserable.

367
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,350
Marrying my brother...

368
00:21:16,010 --> 00:21:18,550
isn't the only way
you can get back at CEO Chae.

369
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:20,450
I still...

370
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:23,720
just don't get why you insist
on marrying my brother.

371
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:26,090
Do you love my brother?

372
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:29,330
- You don't.
- Something like love...

373
00:21:30,260 --> 00:21:32,030
became a luxury I can't afford
a long time ago.

374
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:36,000
And please, Baek Ho,
don't presume to know what's in my heart.

375
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:39,600
I'm asking you.
Stop making things harder on me...

376
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,140
and just give up.

377
00:21:41,770 --> 00:21:42,810
Jang Mi.

378
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:44,510
Jang Mi.

379
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:27,420
Yes.

380
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,090
Alright.

381
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:50,510
- Get out.
- What?

382
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:52,240
How dare you show your face in here?

383
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:54,580
Get out right now.

384
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:56,150
Go...

385
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:59,020
to that Chae Hwa Young
you're so crazy about...

386
00:22:59,450 --> 00:23:01,920
and give her all the comfort she needs,
you filthy bastard!

387
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,690
You think I won't leave
just because you told me to?

388
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:07,190
- I've been miserable this whole time too.
- Exactly.

389
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:10,460
So let's just make a clean break.
There's nothing more to say.

390
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:14,870
After doing something so awful to me,

391
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:17,400
you should be on your hands and knees
begging for forgiveness.

392
00:23:18,070 --> 00:23:19,940
How dare you raise your voice at me?

393
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:21,840
At a time like this,

394
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:25,810
shouldn't you be the one
apologizing to me first?

395
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:29,010
I did feel sorry for hurting you
all this time.

396
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:32,420
But seeing you act like this,
I've lost any sympathy I had.

397
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:34,320
I don't care how angry you were,

398
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,650
but how could you act like
that to Hwa Young?

399
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:37,720
You have no class.

400
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,320
Hey!

401
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:42,890
You want me to show you
what having no class really is?

402
00:23:43,390 --> 00:23:44,390
You bastard!

403
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:48,100
Is this why you grew your hair out?

404
00:23:48,170 --> 00:23:50,600
So you can pose, thinking you're cool?

405
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,870
Does that tramp Hwa Young just eat it up?

406
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:56,170
Mom, stop it. Mom!

407
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,380
This woman has lost her mind.

408
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:03,580
Don't you try to stop me.

409
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,450
I'm settling things with Kang Nam Bong
once and for all today.

410
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:10,490
After everything I've done for you,

411
00:24:11,490 --> 00:24:13,920
how could you do this to me?

412
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:15,690
I couldn't help it.

413
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:19,760
I know how good you've been to me.
I'd have to be an animal not to.

414
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:23,630
But that and love are
two different things.

415
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,000
- What?
- Hwa Young...

416
00:24:27,370 --> 00:24:28,970
makes me feel alive.

417
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:32,710
It was like my life
was starting all over again.

418
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:35,380
I've never felt anything like this
in my entire life.

419
00:24:36,610 --> 00:24:38,250
Dad, that's enough!

420
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:40,450
So when you were living with me,

421
00:24:41,150 --> 00:24:42,490
did it feel like you were already dead?

422
00:24:43,350 --> 00:24:46,520
And with that tramp Hwa Young,
you feel so alive you could just burst?

423
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:49,160
Stop calling her a tramp. It's vulgar.

424
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,360
She means the world to me.

425
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:54,630
- Kang Nam Bong!
- I couldn't help it!

426
00:24:55,370 --> 00:24:57,600
Do you have any idea how hard
I tried to fight these feelings?

427
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:00,800
Do you even realize...

428
00:25:01,910 --> 00:25:04,170
what you're doing to me right now?

429
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:11,250
It's not just a knife
that can make you bleed.

430
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:12,980
Right now,

431
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:19,090
you're murdering me
by tearing my heart to shreds.

432
00:25:21,290 --> 00:25:24,560
Can't you see my heart is bleeding out?

433
00:25:26,630 --> 00:25:31,230
How could you say that?

434
00:25:33,540 --> 00:25:34,570
I told you.

435
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:36,870
I couldn't help it.

436
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,780
I never imagined...

437
00:25:39,310 --> 00:25:41,280
I'd ever feel this way.

438
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:44,050
All this time,

439
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:46,050
my life was black and white.

440
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:47,450
But after I met Hwa Young,

441
00:25:47,980 --> 00:25:49,620
it was suddenly in full color.

442
00:25:51,020 --> 00:25:52,560
I couldn't fight it,

443
00:25:52,620 --> 00:25:55,090
and I was going mad from the torment!

444
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:58,460
But I felt something so vivid.

445
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,900
Is it a mortal sin to feel that way?

446
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:12,480
Come on, Mom!

447
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:14,110
Mom!

448
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:16,710
Mom!

449
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:17,980
What?

450
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:20,020
Baek Ho's mom found out about
Professor Kang's affair...

451
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:21,480
with Chae Hwa Young?

452
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:25,320
Yes. I don't know if the wedding
can even happen now.

453
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:27,660
Frankly, I hope
your wedding is called off,

454
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:29,230
and you get back together with Baek Ho.

455
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:34,230
A part of me wants this wedding called off
so I can go back to Baek Ho.

456
00:26:35,070 --> 00:26:38,130
But then, when I think about
getting revenge for Mom, Dad, and Seo Rin,

457
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,940
I know I have to go through
with this marriage.

458
00:26:43,910 --> 00:26:44,910
Mom.

459
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,780
Tae Pyung.

460
00:26:49,250 --> 00:26:51,820
Suk Hee's head hurts.

461
00:26:51,820 --> 00:26:54,080
Tae Pyung, is Mom's head hurting?

462
00:26:54,150 --> 00:26:56,450
She's been saying her head hurts
for a while now.

463
00:26:56,890 --> 00:26:58,660
I think I should take her
to the doctor tomorrow.

464
00:26:59,420 --> 00:27:01,460
Suk Hee's head hurts.

465
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:04,360
Twins...

466
00:27:04,930 --> 00:27:06,300
Where are the twins?

467
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:10,330
Mom, are you remembering the twins?

468
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:16,710
I miss Jang Mi.

469
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,940
Jang Mi is so pretty.

470
00:27:28,590 --> 00:27:30,790
What will I do if this wedding
falls through?

471
00:27:31,290 --> 00:27:34,490
If that happens,
I can't give Dream to my Jun Ho.

472
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:36,530
What am I supposed to do?

473
00:28:04,390 --> 00:28:06,060
(The First Man)

474
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:07,690
I'm sorry, Young Ja.

475
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:09,090
Are you even human?

476
00:28:09,360 --> 00:28:12,300
You and that tramp,
Chae Hwa Young, are garbage.

477
00:28:12,530 --> 00:28:15,430
It looks like Jang Mi is marrying
Kang Jun Ho after all.

478
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:18,700
Suk Hee is having a lot of dreams lately.

479
00:28:18,970 --> 00:28:22,310
Could Mom's memory be really coming back?

480
00:28:22,770 --> 00:28:23,970
What is this?

481
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:26,880
I think you need to see this, Chairman.

482
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:29,750
It's an alimony lawsuit!

483
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:31,580
What is all this?

484
00:28:36,150 --> 00:28:38,150
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
